    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "exactly. it feels less like a reward and more like they're trying to keep me in a \"goldfish bowl.\" like, i'm more visible now, more monitored. if i'm in a corner office, i'm easier to track. i've even noticed my assistant seems a bit too helpful, almost like they're screening my incoming calls or something. do you think companies actually use promotions like this to neutralize people who might be whistleblowers?",
